record_data.record_narrative_name: PNM Electric Coordination Tariff No. 1, FERC Electric Tariff Volume No. 5 (Section 1)
record_data.record_plain_text: PUBLIC SERVICE COMPANY OF NEW MEXICO Electric Coordination Tariff No. 1 (Section No. 1) FERC Electric Tariff Volume No. 5 PUBLIC SERVICE COMPANY OF NEW MEXICO Electric Coordination Tariff No. 1 General Terms and Conditions 1. RECITALS Public Service Company of New Mexico (PNM or Company) is an electric utility witha New Mexico retail service territory and a transmission network that interconnectswith a variety of other transmission owners in the southwestern United States. This Tariff is intended to permit "Electric Utilities" (as defined below) to acquireCoordination Services from PNM for resale. Coordination Services shall includewholesale Economy Energy transactions at tariff rates and wholesale Firm SystemCapacity/Energy Sale or Exchange transactions at either negotiated or tariff rates. AService Agreement between the Company and the Purchaser shall be executed byeach Party desiring to obtain service pursuant to this Tariff. This Tariff does notsupersede or replace any existing Power or Energy sales agreements or contracts towhich PNM is a party, except that all future Economy Energy transactions will takeplace under this unbundled Tariff rather than under any existing Service Agreementthat bundles transmission and Economy Energy service. Further, PNM may, at itssole option, choose to offer service under PNM's Power and Energy Sales Tariff orthis Tariff as an alternative to arrangements through the Western Systems PowerPool, the Inland Power Pool or any successors to those organizations or otherorganizations that may provide service using PNM's system. 1.3 Nothing contained in this Tariff shall be construed to establish any precedent for anyother agreement nor shall it grant any rights to or impose any obligations on any Partybeyond the scope and term of this Tariff. Agreement to the terms of this Tariff or toany of its Service Schedules shall not obligate PNM to sell any specific quantity ofPower or Energy to any party and shall not obligate any party to purchase any specificquantity of Power or Energy from PNM, except as explicitly provided in any executedService Agreement. Nothing contained in this Tariff shall obligate PNM to constructany new facilities, unless explicitly provided for in a Service Agreement executedpursuant to this Tariff. 2. DEFINITIONS The following terms shall have the following meanings when used in this Tariff: Authorized Representative(s) means person(s) designated by the Parties in the ServiceAgreement or designated on a transaction by transaction or other basis to coordinatethe administration of transactions under this Tariff. Authorized Representatives shallhave no authority to amend any of the provisions of this Tariff. Banked Energy is Energy delivered by PNM to Purchaser or by Purchaser to PNM forrepayment in Energy, rather than cash, at a later date and/or alternative Point(s) ofDelivery. Banked Transaction is a transaction for which the Parties have mutually agreed thatrepayment for Energy provided will be from Banked Energy. Capacity means the instantaneous ability to create Power and Energy. Capacity is an unbundled generation related service and does not include the capability to deliver Energy through PNM's transmission system or the transmission systems of third parties. Capacity shall be sold and purchased in increments of whole megawatts. Control Area means a system or pool capable of adjusting its generation toinstantaneously meet demand, maintain scheduled frequency, and meet its interchangeschedule and frequency bias obligations with the interconnected systems. A "ControlArea" has the ability to account for interchange schedules and inadvertent flows ofEnergy. Economy Energy is Energy sold, Banked or Exchanged on an interruptible basispursuant to the conditions set forth in Service Schedule A of this Tariff. 2.7 Energy means the quantity of electricity produced or consumed over a period of time and measured in kilowatt hours (kWh) or megawatt hours (MWh). Energy is an unbundled generation related service. Electric Utility(ies) means a private or public corporation, marketer, governmentalagency or authority (such as a tribal utility authority or a federal power marketingagency), municipality, rural electric membership corporation or cooperative, or lawfulassociation of any of the foregoing, that sells electric Energy at wholesale or retail;provided, however, that the term "Purchaser" shall not include ultimate consumers ofelectric utility service, nor shall it include electric distribution systems established toserve ultimate consumers formerly served by PNM, if such systems were establishedas a means to facilitate transmission service for ultimate consumers. 2.9 Exchange means simultaneous delivery of Energy between the Parties at differingPoint(s) of Delivery. FERC means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission or its regulatory successor. Firm System Capacity/Energy or Exchange Service means a transaction wherebyPNM has agreed to sell or Exchange and Purchaser has agreed to buy or Exchangefor a specified period, available Capacity with or without associated Energy pursuantto Service Schedule B. Good Utility Practice means any of the practices, methods and acts engaged in orapproved by a significant portion of the electric utility industry during the relevanttime period, or any of the practices, methods and acts which, in the exercise ofreasonable judgment in light of the facts known at the time the decision was made,could have been expected to accomplish the desired result at the lowest reasonablecost consistent with reliability, safety and expedition. Good Utility Practice is notintended to be limited to the optimum practice, method or act to the exclusion of allothers, but rather to be a spectrum of acceptable practices, methods or acts. Incremental Cost means PNM's incremental costs, with respect to Power and Energygenerated on PNM's system, including, but not limited to fuel, labor, operations andmaintenance, generator start-ups, fuel handling, purchased Energy, taxes and anyother variable costs incurred in supplying wholesale Energy. Notice of Request means a request by Purchaser to PNM for purchase of Powerand/or Energy under one of the Service Schedules to this Tariff. A Notice ofRequest may be transmitted to PNM either by telephone, facsimile, PNM's electronicinformation network, or in written form. Open Access Transmission Tariff means PNM's Open Access Transmission Tariff orthe Open Access Transmission Tariff of a third party as each is on file with the FERCand in effect from time to time. Party/Parties means any party or parties to a Service Agreement executed pursuant tothis Tariff, including PNM or any Purchaser. Power means available electric Capacity measured in kilowatts (kW) or megawatts (MW). Power and Energy Sales means any sales of Power or Energy subject to market-based rates under PNM's Power and Energy Sales Tariff as on file with the FERCand in effect from time to time (the Power and Energy Sales Tariff). Point of Delivery means a point of interconnection at PNM's generation source or onPNM's transmission and/or distribution system, at which PNM delivers Power and/or Energy to Purchaser, as established in the Service Agreement or such other points as the Authorized Representatives may agree upon, from time to time. 2.20 Power Marketing Department means that PNM department or organizationresponsible for the sale of electric Capacity and Energy at wholesale in interstatecommerce. Purchaser means any Electric Utility as defined in Section 2.8 of this Tariff whichagrees to buy from or Exchange with PNM any service pursuant to a ServiceSchedule included under this Tariff. Service Agreement means a contract under which PNM and a Purchaser agree totransact pursuant to this Tariff, under PNM's Power and Energy Sales Tariff orunder PNM's Open Access Transmission Tariff. PNM and Purchaser may mutuallyagree to transact under PNM's Power and Energy Sales Tariff or under one or moreService Schedules included under this Tariff. PNM shall have the sole discretion tooffer service under PNM's Power and Energy Sales Tariff or under one or more ofthe Service Schedules included under this Tariff and Purchaser shall have the solediscretion to accept or reject such service. Any transmission service required fordelivery of any transaction under this Tariff or PNM's Power and Energy Sales Tariffshall take place under PNM's Open Access Transmission Tariff or the Open AccessTransmission Tariffs of third parties, pursuant to the conditions set forth in FERC'sOrders 888 and 889, as amended. 2.23 Service Schedule means a schedule of services established pursuant to Section 3 ofthis Tariff. 2.24 System Operations Personnel means the PNM department or organizationresponsible for operating PNM's transmission system and administering the termsand conditions of PNM's Open Access Transmission Tariff. 2.25 Return Date means the date by which Purchaser must begin to return to PNM thePower and/or Energy provided by PNM under PNM's Power and Energy SalesTariff or under one or more of the Service Schedules included under this Tariff, or bywhich PNM must return to Purchaser, where an Exchange or Banked transaction hasbeen executed. 2.26 Tariff means this document, including the attached Service Schedules, as may be amended from time to time. Where service is provided at a negotiated rate under PNM's Power and Energy Sales Tariff, Tariff shall be understood to refer to that document. However, in all cases billing under any Service Agreement shall be in accordance with Section 8 of this Tariff. 3. SERVICES TO BE PROVIDED UNDER THIS TARIFF 3.1 PNM shall maintain the exclusive right to determine the amount, time, and the availability of Power and/or Energy to be sold or Exchanged under this Tariff. PNM may choose to offer and Purchaser may choose to take service under one or more of the attached Service Schedules: Service Schedule A describes the terms and conditions of the sale or Exchange ofcoordination Power and Energy as an unbundled Economy Energy Service. Service Schedule B describes the terms and conditions of the sale or Exchange ofcoordination Power and Energy as an unbundled Firm System Capacity/Energy Saleor Exchange Service. PNM may, from time to time, add Service Schedules to this Tariff or delete ServiceSchedules from this Tariff. The type of service, amount of service, transaction length, Points of Delivery,compensation, and other pertinent characteristics of service shall be determined inadvance of any transaction and shall be confirmed in a Service Agreement, the formof which is attached hereto as Attachment 1. When an executed Service Agreementbetween PNM and the Purchaser exists, the Authorized Representatives or designeesmay mutually agree to modify the Points of Delivery or other conditions of service byverbal agreement prior to the commencement of a specific transaction. Sucharrangements shall be confirmed in writing at the earliest mutually agreeableopportunity but in no case more than 30 days after the transaction has commenced. Service under this Tariff shall not be available to any retail customer of PNM. Services similar to the services under this Tariff may also be available under PNM'sPower and Energy Sales Tariff and nothing in this Tariff shall limit PNM's ability to offer service under PNM's Power and Energy Sales Tariff as opposed to one or more of the Service Schedules under this Tariff. 4. CONDITIONS OF SERVICE 4.1 Energy delivered by the Company pursuant to this Tariff will be delivered at any existing Point of Delivery that is mutually agreed to by the Parties subject to the requirement to obtain any required transmission service and ancillary services separately under PNM's Open Access Transmission Tariff and/or the Open Access Transmission Tariffs of third parties. In the alternative the Purchaser may obtain transmission service and ancillary services from any Independent System Operator (ISO) that may be able to make such service available. Unless otherwise agreed, the Purchaser has the complete responsibility for acquiring transmission from the Point of Delivery to the Purchaser's final delivery point. If Purchaser requires transmission service on PNM's system, Purchaser shall be required to secure any required transmission and ancillary services from PNM's System Operations Department on its own behalf, except as provided in Section 4.3.If Purchaser obtains the required transmission and ancillary services, PNM shall file a Service Agreement with the FERC placing the Purchaser under PNM's Open Access Transmission Tariff. All pertinent arrangements for such services can be made directly between Purchaser and PNM's System Operations Department personnel. In the alternative, Purchaser may request that PNM's Power Marketing Department secure all transmission and ancillary services required to effect service to Purchaser under PNMs Open Access Transmission Tariff. PNM's Power Marketing Department shall have the option to decline such requests. If PNM's Power Marketing Department secures the required transmission and related services, a Service Agreement under PNM's Open Access Transmission Tariff shall be filed with the FERC, if service is not covered by an existing Service Agreement. 4.4 The Purchaser shall be financially responsible for any third party impacts related to any transactions under this Tariff, including but not limited to unscheduled transmission flows. 4.5 PNM does not warrant that it has any Power and Energy available to sell and does not commit to enter into any individual transaction with any party under this Tariff. All transactions under this Tariff are subject to the availability of Power and Energy to be determined at PNM's sole discretion. 4.6 PNM shall provide service under the Tariff only to Purchasers that have signed a Service Agreement for the requested service, except that service may commence prior to completing a Service Agreement if the Parties mutually agree and execute a Service Agreement within a reasonable period of time after service has commenced. In the event that the Purchaser has not signed a Service Agreement within a reasonable time period, PNM shall file an unexecuted Service Agreement with the FERC. All arrangements for transactions provided under this Tariff shall be made between Authorized Representatives of PNM and Purchaser or their respective designees. PNM shall maintain appropriate documentation for each transaction, including requests to preschedule Energy deliveries, starting time and date, price, duration, quantity, delivery point, and description of service provided. 4.7 In the event that Purchaser is a public utility subject to the jurisdiction of the FERC, any Banked Transaction or Exchange that uses the transmission system of Purchaser shall use the Open Access Transmission Tariff of Purchaser for the unbundled transmission and ancillary service components of such Banked Transaction or Exchange. Purchaser or PNM shall secure the necessary services under Purchaser's Open Access Transmission Tariff as the Parties shall agree. PRIORITY OF SERVICE - The priority of service obligations in this Tariff shall apply only to the provision of unbundled Power and Energy. All priority of service provisions of PNM's Open Access Transmission Tariff shall apply separately. Specific terms and conditions relating to the priority of service, interruption, and curtailment may be established in a specific Service Agreement. In the absence of such terms and conditions relating to the priority of service in a specific Service Agreement, PNM's native load and long term contractual commitments shall have priority over any services or Exchanges being rendered under this Tariff. 6. SCHEDULING 6.1 Unless otherwise agreed by the Parties, the Purchaser shall use its best efforts to provide hourly schedules of all deliveries of Power and Energy to PNM's schedulers or system dispatchers by not later than 9:00 AM Mountain Standard Time (MST) of the day prior to the day of delivery, except in the case of spot market transactions. If Purchaser requires service and has been unable to provide hourly schedules by 9:00 AM MST of the day prior to delivery, PNM will use its best efforts to accommodate such requests, subject to the availability of Power and Energy and Purchaser's ability (or PNM's Power Marketing Department's ability to obtain transmission service when it obtains transmission service under this Tariff as provided in Section 4.3) to secure any required transmission service from PNM's System Operations Department and/or third parties. If such prescheduled deliveries of Power and Energy are actually interrupted or curtailed by PNM, the Preschedules shall be adjusted to reflect such interruption or curtailment of service. Where appropriate a pro rata adjustment to the applicable billing charge shall be made to reflect the period(s) of interruption or curtailment. Purchaser will respond to all reasonable requests by PNM to verify schedules within one day of receiving such requests. 7. TERM AND TERMINATION 7.1 This Tariff may be terminated unilaterally and at any time by PNM on proper notice to the FERC, subject to any requisite action by the FERC. Any Service Agreement executed pursuant to this Tariff may be terminated unilaterally at any time by PNM or the Purchaser in accordance with the requirements of the FERC, this Tariff, and the applicable Service Agreement. Termination of this Tariff or any Service Agreement shall not result in the termination of any service provided under a Service Agreement executed prior to the expiration of such Service Agreement entered into prior to the termination of this Tariff. Service provided under any Service Agreement entered into subject to this Tariff shall not obligate PNM to provide any continuing service beyond the expiration date of such Service Agreement. If payment is not received by PNM by the due date specified in Section 8.3 or return of Banked Energy has not commenced by the Return Date as defined in Section 2.25, PNM may elect to terminate all services under this Tariff provided under a Service Agreement. PNM shall provide FERC and the Purchaser with fifteen (15) days written notice of its intent to terminate the service. Termination shall not relieve the Purchaser of its obligation to pay any amounts due PNM or to return any Power and Energy due PNM through an Exchange for services rendered prior to termination. 8. BILLINGS AND PAYMENTS 8.1 Bills for payment for Power and Energy sales made under this Tariff shall be rendered monthly. Specific items for billing purposes shall be determined by PNM and Purchaser based on the nature of the service rendered. Billing and payments with respect to sales under this Tariff shall be based upon PNM's records of the amounts of service rendered. 8.2 Bills for amounts payable for any month shall be prepared and submitted via facsimile or other electronic means mutually agreed to by the Parties no later than ten (10) days after the end of the month in which the service was provided. Bills shall be due and payable on the day the Purchaser receives the bill and shall become delinquent after the fifteenth (15th) calendar day (Due Date) from the date the Purchaser receives the bill. Should the Due Date fall on a weekend or holiday, the payment shall be due by the first weekday thereafter that is not a holiday. Amounts not received on or before the Due Date shall be payable with interest accrued from the Due Date to the date of payment and shall be calculated in accordance with the methodology specified for interest on refunds in the Commission's regulations at 18 C.F.R. § 35.19a(a)(2)(iii). 8.3 If payment has not been received within fifteen (15) days from the Due Date, PNMwill provide notice to the Purchaser that the Purchaser is in default and PNM may discontinue any further service, after providing notification to the FERC. The default will be deemed to have been cured upon payment by the Purchaser of all amounts in said notice, plus accrued interest through the date of payment. 8.4 The Purchaser shall have the right to challenge or dispute any bill or statement during a time period not greater than one (1) month following the rendering of the bill. Such challenge shall relate to the accuracy of the computation of the bill or the amount of service rendered. Such challenge shall not relate to the rate to be paid for service that was negotiated between PNM and Purchaser as reflected in the Service Agreement or other confirmation. 8.5 If all or any portion of any bill is challenged or disputed, the entire amount shall bepaid on or before the Due Date. Upon determination that the bill amount should becorrected and that a refund is due to Purchaser, PNM shall promptly refund thecorrected amount with interest accrued from the date payment was received by PNMuntil the date of refund. Interest shall be calculated in accordance with themethodology specified for interest on refunds in the Commission's regulations at 18C.F.R. § 35.19a(a)(2)(iii). Adjustments for errors or true up of estimated billings shall be made in subsequent billsat such time as information becomes available to correct the original billing. Paymentsshall be made to PNM by wire transfer or other electronic means mutually agreed toby the Parties to the Payment Account Number stated in the Service Agreement. PNM, at its sole discretion, may require a security deposit or other acceptable financial guarantee as a condition of providing service under this Tariff. If PNM has not required an initial security deposit and Purchaser subsequently has been delinquent in the payment of its bill from PNM, PNM shall have the right, at its option, to require Purchaser to establish a security deposit in an amount not to exceed five times its highest anticipated monthly bill from PNM. Such security deposit will bear interest payable to the Purchaser at the rate for interest on refunds in the Commission's regulations at 18 C.F.R. § 35.19a(a)(2)(iii) until such time as PNM may cancel the security deposit and return the original deposit plus accrued interest to the Purchaser. PNM shall determine the date on which the security deposit must be made and the duration for which it will be maintained. In lieu of such security deposit, PNM may, at its sole discretion, accept a letter of credit or similar financial instrument. PNM may terminate service to Purchaser under this Tariff upon fifteen (15) days written notice, subject to an appropriate filing with FERC, in the event Purchaser does not maintain or replenish the required security deposit within fifteen (15) calendar days after requested by PNM in writing, if all or a portion of the security deposit is applied to cure a delinquency in any payment due from Purchaser. 9. RATE CHANGES - PNM may unilaterally amend or supersede the general terms, conditions and rates in this Tariff or any Service Schedule that is part of this Tariff at any time and from time to time by making the appropriate filing with the FERC and notifying all Purchasers of such change. Any change shall become effective as permitted under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act and the FERC's regulations promulgated thereunder. No such change in filed rates shall have any effect upon any negotiated rate for service unless explicitly agreed to by the Parties. Except as provided in this Section 9, nothing contained herein shall be construed as affecting in any way the right of the party furnishing service under this rate schedule to unilaterally make application to the FERC for a change in rates under section 205 of the Federal Power Act and pursuant to FERC's rules and Regulations promulgated thereunder. 10. UNCONTROLLABLE FORCES - Neither Party shall be considered to be in default in the performance of any of its obligations hereunder other than obligations of a Party to make payment due hereunder, when a failure of performance shall be due to uncontrollable forces. The term "Uncontrollable Forces" shall mean any cause beyond the control of the Party unable to perform such obligations, including, but not limited to, failure of or threat of failure of facilities, flood, earthquake, storm, fire, lightning, and other natural catastrophes; epidemic, war, riot, civil disturbance or disobedience, strike, labor dispute, labor or material shortage, sabotage, government priorities, and restraint by court order or public authority, and action or non-action by or failure to obtain the necessary authorizations or approvals from any governmental or tribal agency or authority, which by exercise of due diligence such Party could not reasonably have been expected to avoid and which by exercise of due diligence it shall be unable to overcome. Nothing contained herein shall be construed as to require either Party to settle any strike or labor dispute in which it may be involved. 11. LIABILITY AND INDEMNITY PNM and Purchaser shall release, defend, and indemnify each other from and againstany and all liability, loss, damage and expense arising, or alleged to arise, from orincidental to, injury or damage to persons or property occasioned by or in connectionwith the operation of their respective facilities or the production or flow of Powerand Energy by or through such facilities, except to the extent such injury or damageor loss is due to the negligence or willful misconduct of the other Party. Purchaser assumes all responsibility for Power and Energy beyond the Point(s) ofDelivery and shall hold harmless and defend PNM from all liability for injuries ordamages to persons or property, resulting from the use or presence of Power andEnergy beyond such Point(s) of Delivery. Purchaser shall indemnify and holdharmless PNM from and against all liability for injuries, loss or damage toPurchaser's customers arising out of electric service to such entities. ASSIGNMENT OF AGREEMENT - Any Service Agreement or other agreement forsales of Power and/or Energy executed under this Tariff shall inure to the benefit of,and shall bind, the successors of the Parties thereto, but shall not be assignablewithout the written consent of said Parties. In the event the Purchaser assigns orresells to another party any portion of the Power and/or Energy purchased hereunder,the Purchaser remains liable to PNM for payment of the full amount of all Power andEnergy sold to the Purchaser hereunder. NON-DEDICATION OF FACILITIES - No service provided by PNM to a Purchaserunder any provision of this Tariff shall constitute the dedication of the system of eitherParty to the other Party, and it is understood and agreed that any such Serviceprovided under any provision of this Tariff shall cease upon the termination of theParties' obligations hereunder. 14. NO THIRD PARTY BENEFICIARIES - This Tariff is intended solely for the benefit of the Parties and nothing herein shall be construed to create any duty to, or standard of care with reference to, or any liability to, or any rights in, any person not a Party. 15. NOTICES - Any formal notice, demand or request provided for in this Tariff or Service Agreement, or served, given or made in connection with it, shall be in writing and shall be deemed properly served, given or made if delivered in person or sent by United States certified or registered mail, postage prepaid, to the persons specified in the Service Agreement. Either Party may at any time and from time to time, by written notice to the other Party, change the designation or address of the person so specified as the one to receive notices pursuant to this Tariff or Service Agreement. 16. GOVERNING LAW - This Tariff and all Service Agreements shall, in all respects, be interpreted and construed and the rights of the Parties shall be governed by New Mexico law, except to the extent that federal law controls. Further, the Parties expressly agree to the jurisdiction of a court located within the State of New Mexico to resolve any disputes hereunder except insofar as the FERC shall have exclusive jurisdiction. 17. DISPUTES - Disputes on any matter relating to this Tariff or to a Service Agreement shall be discussed and resolved by the Authorized Representatives, who shall use their best efforts to amicably and promptly resolve the dispute. Should the Authorized Representatives be unable to resolve the dispute, the matter shall be referred to the Parties' executive officers for resolution. Should the Parties' executive officers fail to reach agreement, the Parties may then seek whatever remedies are available in equity or at law, except as the Parties may have agreed to arbitration or other alternative dispute resolution by placing such provisions in an executed Service Agreement.

record_data.record_title: Service Schedule A – Economy Energy Service
record_data.record_plain_text:
PUBLIC SERVICE COMPANY OF NEW MEXICO Electric Coordination Tariff No. 1 SERVICE SCHEDULE A - ECONOMY ENERGY SERVICE
FERC Electric Tariff Volume No. 5
ELECTRIC COORDINATION TARIFF NO. 1 OF PUBLIC SERVICE COMPANY OF NEW MEXICO SERVICE SCHEDULE A - ECONOMY ENERGY SERVICE A-l DURATION: A-1.1 This Service Schedule, a part of the Tariff, shall become effective on the effective date of the Tariff and shall continue to be effective for the life of the Tariff as provided for in Section 7 of the Tariff. A-2 PURPOSE: The purpose of this Service Schedule A is to define specific procedures, terms and conditions for requesting and providing Economy Energy Service for transactions of one year or less. A-3 SCHEDULING AND DELIVERY: A-3.1 PNM, at its sole discretion, may from time to time have Energy available for sale or Exchange to Purchasers on a non-firm basis for periods of any part of an hour or one or more hours but not more than one year and may, at its sole discretion and subject to agreement with Purchaser, choose to sell, Bank or Exchange such Economy Energy under the provisions of this Service Schedule A. A-3.2 The Purchaser may schedule Economy Energy service from PNM by mutual agreement; provided, however, that each Party shall be the sole judge as to the extent to and the conditions under which it is willing to provide or receive such service hereunder consistent with statutory requirements and contractual commitments. A-3.3 Point(s) of Delivery will be determined by the mutual agreement of PNM and the Purchaser as provided in Section 4.1 of the Tariff and subject to the availability of any required Transmission Service or Ancillary Service. A-3.4 Economy Energy may be interrupted or curtailed by PNM for any reason without notice unless otherwise provided for in a Service Agreement executed pursuant to this Tariff. A-3.5 Services similar to the services offered under this Service Schedule A may be available under PNM's Power and Energy Sales Tariff and nothing in this Service Schedule A shall limit PNM's rights or ability to offer service under PNM's Power and Energy Sales Tariff rather than under this Service Schedule A. A-4 PRICING: A-4.1 The Rates for PNM's sale of Economy Energy Service shall be agreed to by PNM and the Purchaser at the time the transaction is negotiated. Such Rates shall be based on PNM's cost of system generation; provided, however, that the Rates shall not exceed the sum of: A-4.1.1 Up to 100 percent of PNM's Incremental Cost plus 10 percent of Incremental Cost. In no case shall the mark-up above PNM's Incremental Cost exceed the $55.30/per Megawatt hour that PNM would charge if the energy were delivered on a firm basis for a sale price based upon the sale of firm energy pursuant to Service Schedule B. In no case shall the price charged be less than PNM's incremental cost. A-4.1.2 When the sale is made solely from purchased Power not backed by PNM's system, the rate shall not exceed 100 percent of the purchased Power costs plus PNM's additional costs as defined in Section 2.13. A-4.2 In lieu of monetary remuneration, the Parties may mutually agree to Bank or Exchange Economy Energy Service. Terms and conditions of an Exchange transaction including any Exchange ratio and other items as specified in 4.2.1 below shall be set out in the Service Agreement. PNM may have Energy that it is willing to make available on the basis of an Exchange. A-4.2.1 The type of service, ratio of Exchange, amount of Exchange, Return Date, Points of Delivery, and other pertinent characteristics of service shall be determined in advance of any transaction and shall be confirmed in writing in the Service Agreement, Attachment 1 to this Tariff, prior to the transaction or as soon as practical after the transaction has commenced, except that in no case shall PNM file the executed Service Agreement more than 30 days after the transaction has commenced. Unless otherwise specified, the exchange ratio shall be 1 to 1 for energy exchanged during like periods and not greater than 1.5 to 1 for off peak energy returned for energy provided during on peak periods. A-4.3 Purchaser shall, unless otherwise agreed to by the Parties, secure, on its own behalf, transmission and ancillary services, if required, for any transaction from PNM's Transmission Department. If Purchaser obtains the required transmission and ancillary services, PNM shall file a Service Agreement with the FERC placing the Purchaser under PNM's Open Access Transmission Tariff. All pertinent arrangements for such services shall be made directly between Purchaser and PNM's Transmission Department personnel. In the alternative, Purchaser may request that PNM's Power Marketing Department secure all transmission and ancillary services under PNM's Open Access Transmission Tariff ("OATT") required to effect service to Purchaser. PNM's Power Marketing Department shall have the option to decline such requests. If the PNM Power Marketing Department secures all transmission and ancillary services, such transmission and ancillary services shall be secured pursuant to the terms of the PNM OATT and an appropriate OATT Service Agreement shall be filed with the FERC, if required. These rates are subject to change upon change to PNM's Open Access Transmission Tariff and new rates will become effective immediately upon modification of the Open Access Transmission Tariff, after any notification required in the Open Access Transmission Tariff.

record_data.record_title: Service Schedule B – Firm Capacity System Service
record_data.record_plain_text:
PUBLIC SERVICE COMPANY OF NEW MEXICO Electric Coordination Tariff No. 1 SERVICE SCHEDULE B FIRM SYSTEM CAPACITY/ENERGY SALE OR EXCHANGE SERVICE
FERC Electric Tariff Volume No. 5
ELECTRIC COORDINATION TARIFF NO. 1 OF PUBLIC SERVICE COMPANY OF NEW MEXICO SERVICE SCHEDULE B FIRM SYSTEM CAPACITY/ENERGY SALE OR EXCHANGE SERVICE B-l DURATION: This Service Schedule B, a part of the Tariff, shall become effective on the effective date of the Tariff and shall continue to be effective for the life of the Tariff as provided for in Section 7 of the Tariff. B-2 PURPOSE: The purpose of this Service Schedule B is to define specific procedures, terms and conditions for requesting and providing Firm System Capacity/Energy Sale or Exchange Service for transactions of one year or less. B-3 SCHEDULING AND DELIVERY: B-3.1 PNM may sell or Exchange Firm System Capacity/Energy Service when PNM deems such service to be available. At its sole discretion, PNM may choose to sell or Exchange such Firm System Capacity/Energy Service under the terms of this Service Schedule B. Prior to each delivery of Firm System Capacity/Energy Service, the starting time and date, price, duration, quantity and delivery point(s) therefor shall be determined by PNM and the Purchaser. B-3.2 The Purchaser may schedule Firm System Capacity/Energy Service from PNM by mutual agreement; provided, however, that each Party shall be the sole judge as to the extent to and the conditions under which it is willing to provide or receive such service hereunder consistent with statutory requirements and contractual commitments and subject to the availability of any required Transmission Service or Ancillary Service. B-3.3 Once agreement has been reached, then the obligation for Firm System Capacity/Energy Service becomes a firm commitment, for both Parties, for the agreed upon service and terms. B-3.4 Firm System Capacity transactions shall include buying, selling, or exchanging Capacity between Parties with or without associated Energy. Firm Capacity is deemed a Capacity sale from PNM's system resources and backed by PNM's Capacity reserves. B-3.5 Firm Energy transactions shall include buying, selling or exchanging firm Energy between Parties. Subject to mutual agreement, firm Energy is deemed a quantity of Energy PNM has agreed to sell or Exchange and Purchaser has agreed to buy or Exchange within a specified time period. B-3.6 Firm Capacity shall be Capacity which is interruptible by PNM only under any of the following conditions: (a) Within the recall time agreed to by PNM and Purchaser, (b) To prevent system separation during an emergency; provided, however, that PNM has exercised all prudent operating alternatives prior to the interruption or curtailment, (c) To meet its public utility or statutory obligations to its customers or (d) under the conditions specified in Section 10 of this Tariff. B-3.7 When supplying firm Energy, PNM shall use reasonable efforts, including purchasing available Energy from other utilities. B-3.8 Services similar to the services offered under this Service Schedule B may be available under PNM's Power and Energy Sales Tariff and nothing in this Service Schedule B shall limit PNM's rights or ability to offer service under PNM's Power and Energy Sales Tariff rather than under this Service Schedule B. B-4 PRICING: B-4.1 The Rates for PNM's sale of Firm System Capacity/Energy Service shall be agreed to by PNM and the Purchaser at the time the transaction is negotiated. Such Rates shall be based on PNM's cost of system generation; provided, however, that the Rates shall not exceed the sum of: B-4.1.1 A negotiated Energy charge that shall not exceed PNM's forecasted Incremental Cost plus a negotiated demand charge of up to: $230.03/kW/year, $ 19.17/kW/month, $ 4.42/kW/week, or $ 0.88/kW/day, subject to a cap of the weekly rate times the highest demand experienced on any day in a period of seven consecutive days. $ 0.0553/kW/hr, subject to a cap of the daily rate for any consecutive period of service longer than 16 hours in any day.
B4.1.2 In no case shall the price charged be less than PNM's incremental cost.
B-4.2 In lieu of monetary remuneration, such Parties may mutually agree to Exchange Firm System Capacity/Energy Service. Terms and conditions of an Exchange transaction including any exchange ratio and other items as specified in 4.2.1 below shall be set out in the Service Agreement and as provided in Section 3.2 of the Tariff. B-4.2.1 PNM may have Power and Energy that it is willing to make available on the basis of an Exchange under this Service Schedule B rather than under. PNM's Power and Energy Sales Tariff. The type of service, ratio of Exchange, Amount of Exchange, Return Date, Points of Delivery and other pertinent characteristics of service shall be determined in advance of any transaction and shall be confirmed in writing in the Service Agreement, Attachment 1 to this Tariff, prior to the transaction or as soon as practical after the transaction has commenced. Unless otherwise specified, the exchange ratio shall be 1 to 1 for energy exchanged during like periods and not greater than 1.5 to 1 for off peak energy returned for energy provided during on peak periods. B-4.2.2 The type of service, ratio of Exchange, amount of Exchange, Return Date, Points of Delivery, and other pertinent characteristics of service shall be determined in advance of any transaction and shall be confirmed in a Service Agreement as provided in Section 3.2 of the Tariff. B-4.3 Purchaser shall be required, unless the Parties otherwise agree, to secure, on its own behalf, transmission and ancillary services, if required, for any transaction from PNM's Transmission Department. If Purchaser obtains the required transmission and ancillary services, PNM shall file a Service Agreement with the FERC placing the Purchaser under PNM's Open Access Transmission Tariff. All pertinent arrangements for such services can be made directly with PNM's Transmission Department personnel. In the alternative, Purchaser may request that PNM's Power Marketing Department secure all transmission and ancillary services under PNM's Open Access Transmission Tariff ("OATT") required to effect service to Purchaser. PNM's Power Marketing Department shall have the option to decline such requests. If the PNM Power Marketing Department secures all transmission and ancillary services, such transmission and ancillary services shall be secured pursuant to the terms of PNM OATT and an appropriate OATT Service Agreement shall be filed with the FERC, if required. These rates are subject to change upon change to PNM's OATT and new rates will become effective immediately upon modification of the OATT, after any notification required in the OATT.
